  "body": "I recently developed by using React, but i found that can't change the element's CSS (the value of certain fields or class name) from a loop result. For example:\n\n``` js\nconst {data} = this.props;\n\nmap(data, (result, index) => \n  <div key={index} className=\"result-main animated bounceIn\">\n    <div className=\"result-content\">{result.name}</div>\n    <span \n      className=\"result-remove\"\n      onClick={() => this.handleRemove(result.id)}\n    >X</span>\n  </div>\n)\n```\n\nnow, i want to remove an element via `handleRemove(param)` and change its class name like: `bounceIn` change into `bounceOut`, to produce an animation effects. Is there any way to help me to solve this?\n\nExpecting your answer! \n",
